ENTRY            E1890   20260227   20260508   20260508       E157
SUBENT        E1890001   20260227   20260508   20260508       E157
BIB                 14         43
TITLE      Precise measurement of the cross section of
           3He(3He,2p)4He by using 3He doubly charged beam
AUTHOR     (N.Kudomi, M.Komori, K.Takahisa, S.Yoshida, K.Kume,
            H.Ohsumi, T.Itahashi)
INSTITUTE  (2JPNOSA,2JPNIRS,2JPNWER)
           (2JPNJPN) Saga University, Saga
REFERENCE  (J,PR/C,69,015802,2004)
           Main reference. See also TITLE and AUTHOR.
           (J,NP/A,718,466,2003)
           T.Itahashi+, Proc. of the Seventh International
           Symposium on Nuclei in the Cosmos (NIC7)
PART-DET   (P,A)
INC-SOURCE - Beam intensity is 200 uA.
           - Charge of incident ion is 2+.
INC-SPECT  EN: Effective reaction energy has 0.15% error, taking
           into account accuracy of 0.1% for acceleration
           voltage, 10% for stopping power, and 0.09% for energy
           spread in target
SAMPLE     - Chemical-form of target is element.
           - Physical-form of target is gas. (Windowless gas
             target consists of a differential pumping and gas
             circulation/purification system)
           - Target-thickness: 0.75 Torr
METHOD     (COINC) Detect proton, proton and alpha in
                   coincidence.
           (EDE) 4 delta E-E counter telescopes
FACILITY   (ACCEL,2JPNOSA) NANOGUN ECR ion source with specially
                           designed ceramic insulator
DETECTOR   (SOLST) Delta E counters with FWHM of 100-120 keV for
                   5.48 MeV alpha particle
           (SOLST) E counters with FWHM of 70-100 keV for 5.48
                   MeV alpha particle
ERR-ANALYS (ERR-1) Uncertainty in reaction energy
           (ERR-2) Uncertainty in beam intensity
           (ERR-3) Uncertainty in target density
           (ERR-4) Uncertainty in detection efficiency
REL-REF    (N,,T.Itahashi+,J,RSI,69,1032,1998)
           Performance and design of ion source
           (N,,T.Itahashi+,J,RSI,71,1075,2000)
           Performance and design of ion source
HISTORY    (20040416C) Kc + On
           (20061004A) On. Reference (NIC7) added.
           (20251112U) On. Minor revision in 002-003.
ENDBIB              43
COMMON               4          3
ERR-1      ERR-2      ERR-3      ERR-4
PER-CENT   PER-CENT   PER-CENT   PER-CENT
 0.15       2.         1.3        3.
ENDCOMMON            3
ENDSUBENT           50
SUBENT        E1890002   20260227   20260508   20260508       E157
BIB                  3          3
REACTION   (2-HE-3(HE3,2P)2-HE-4,,SIG)
STATUS     (TABLE,,N.Kudomi+,J,PR/C,69,015802,2004) Table 2
HISTORY    (20080131A) On. Unit corrected (MB -> B)
ENDBIB               3
NOCOMMON             0          0
DATA                 2          8
EN-CM      DATA
KEV        B
       31.2   2.46E-10
       33.1   4.52E-10
       35.2   9.46E-10
       37.3   1.83E-09
       39.3   3.44E-09
       41.3   5.79E-09
       43.3   9.55E-09
       45.3   1.53E-08
ENDDATA             10
ENDSUBENT           18
SUBENT        E1890003   20260227   20260508   20260508       E157
BIB                  5         15
REACTION   (2-HE-3(HE3,2P)2-HE-4,,SIG,,SFC)
ERR-ANALYS (ERR-SYS) Total systematic uncertainty
           (ERR-S) Statistical uncertainty
CRITIQUE   N.Otuka (2025-11-12): The S-factor cannot be derived
           from the cross section in 002. It is likely that the
           authors set the atomic weight of 3He to 3 amu in
           derivation of the S-factor. (The first author
           confirmed that the S-factor was derived from the cross
           section in 002.)
REL-REF    (A,,A.Krauss+,J,NP/A,467,273,1987)
           The accuracy of both statistical and systematic
           uncertainties of the present measurement is better
           than that in this work.
STATUS     (TABLE,,N.Kudomi+,J,PR/C,69,015802,2004) Table 2
           (DEP,E1890002) Cross section
ENDBIB              15
COMMON               1          3
ERR-SYS
PER-CENT
 3.8
ENDCOMMON            3
DATA                 3          8
EN-CM      DATA       ERR-S
KEV        B*MEV      B*MEV
       31.2       6.40       0.39
       33.1       5.48       0.22
       35.2       5.62       0.21
       37.3       5.46       0.20
       39.3       5.69       0.25
       41.3       5.51       0.18
       43.3       5.43       0.14
       45.3       5.39       0.09
ENDDATA             10
